    "Completed forms are evaluated by RECs, and their evaluations are articulated (using National Statement concepts) with the intent that researchers will respond to them. 4.",
    "Researchers then conduct research, within the scope of their REC approval, and ongoing commitment to ethical practice (which may be further informed by disciplinary and cultural norms). 5.",
    "Journal editors and reviewers, funders, and RECs, will then review submissions at different levels of granularity regarding the completed work, for internal or external reporting/dissemination.",
    "These should include reference to the REC process (at minimum reporting that one was completed), and any issues arising.Therefore, to map the material ethics ecosystem we conducted a review of:1.",
    "Resources available institutionally, to be drawn on by the REC process. 2."
